00:29.840 --> 00:35.282
[traffic honking and rushing]

00:35.283 --> 00:36.936
Mr. Pembridge?

00:36.937 --> 00:38.471
Mr. Pembridge? Mr. Pembridge?

00:38.472 --> 00:40.173
I'm just a little delicate.

00:40.174 --> 00:41.732
- How was your flight?
- Oh, which part,

00:41.733 --> 00:43.602
sitting on the tarmac in
New York for three hours

00:43.603 --> 00:47.439
or spending the night on
a marble floor in Houston?

00:47.440 --> 00:49.573
Morning, darling.

00:49.574 --> 00:51.491
Did you sleep well?

00:51.492 --> 00:52.738
Like a princess.

00:52.739 --> 00:56.118
Mm, that's not what it sounded like.

00:56.119 --> 00:57.749
Why, was I snoring?

00:57.750 --> 01:01.130
Mm, yeah, just like a little
squirrel I had when I was child.

01:01.131 --> 01:03.024
- It was like...
- Oh, no. Come on, stop.

01:03.025 --> 01:06.165
Oh, it's so embarrassing.

01:06.166 --> 01:09.066
No, don't be. Mm-mm, you're adorable.

01:09.067 --> 01:12.816
You're just... You are adorable.

01:17.100 --> 01:18.457
Hmm...

01:18.854 --> 01:24.618
and you are a wonderfully
unexpected surprise,

01:25.492 --> 01:29.519
but you probably should get
going before somebody sees you.

01:29.520 --> 01:33.091
Well, if I'm such wonderful
surprise, why should I sneak

01:33.092 --> 01:36.784
out of your room like a peasant
leaving his master's dacha?

01:36.785 --> 01:38.295
That's ridiculous.

01:38.296 --> 01:39.781
- [knock on door]
- There's a... oh, God, oh, hide.

01:39.782 --> 01:41.124
Hide under the bed.

01:41.125 --> 01:42.706
I'm a man, I'm not
gonna hide under the bed.

01:42.707 --> 01:44.505
Then... then... then get in the closet.

01:44.506 --> 01:45.895
- Pavel, Pavel...
- No, okay, will you...

01:45.896 --> 01:49.108
Please, we'll talk about it later, okay?

01:49.109 --> 01:52.187
All right, come... coming.

01:54.864 --> 01:56.685
Oh, Thomas, you made it.

01:56.686 --> 01:57.956
Oh, tell that to the hotel.

01:57.957 --> 01:59.922
They've given away my fucking room.

01:59.923 --> 02:02.727
You know, I haven't bathed
or slept or had a decent meal

02:02.728 --> 02:04.454
in the last 48 hours.

02:04.455 --> 02:05.869
I'm totally shagged out.

02:05.870 --> 02:08.889
I mean... and to boot,
they lost my suitcase.

02:08.890 --> 02:11.407
I'm sorry, darling, but
do you mind if I just

02:11.408 --> 02:13.325
put my head down for five minutes?

02:13.326 --> 02:15.028
I don't... oh, I'm so tired.

02:15.029 --> 02:16.946
Yes, yes, you should rest.

02:16.947 --> 02:19.823
Get some rest because
our meeting with Delgado

02:19.824 --> 02:22.725
is not for three hours.

02:22.726 --> 02:24.307
- Oh, well.
- Yeah.

02:24.308 --> 02:27.184
Not good form to keep a
billionaire waiting, huh?

02:27.185 --> 02:28.503
No.

02:28.504 --> 02:30.853
Don't forget to wake me.

02:30.854 --> 02:32.340
Nope.

02:32.341 --> 02:33.466
Hey, meet me in the lobby at 6:30.

02:33.467 --> 02:34.713
We got a cab to the restaurant.

02:34.714 --> 02:36.176
- Perfect, can't wait.
- Maestro.

02:36.177 --> 02:37.591
"Hai Lai," awesome playing last night.

02:37.592 --> 02:38.885
Thank you.

02:38.886 --> 02:40.636
It was sexy, but it was not
together, not together, eh?

02:40.637 --> 02:42.410
And well done for not
eating those carnitas, Bob.

02:42.411 --> 02:45.072
Yeah, that was also not
together. Dee Dee, what's up?

02:45.073 --> 02:46.822
Checking out the Frida Kahlo museum.

02:46.823 --> 02:48.404
Man, that lady does some tricky shit.

02:48.405 --> 02:51.737
Yeah, yeah, check out...
check out the [inaudible].

02:51.738 --> 02:52.888
- Whoa, baby. [inaudible].
- How are you doing?

02:52.889 --> 02:54.567
Good, yes. Hey. Muy bien.

02:54.568 --> 02:55.885
Do you want to hear what we're doing today?

02:55.886 --> 02:57.660
Yes, tell me. "Hai Lai," tell me.

02:57.661 --> 02:59.698
Okay, first we have a press
conference until 11:00.

02:59.699 --> 03:01.448
Then you have a photo op with Miss Cancun.

03:01.449 --> 03:02.887
- Is that Miss Cancun?
- That is.

03:02.888 --> 03:05.692
Then you have the big meeting
with Juan Luis Delgado.

03:05.693 --> 03:08.042
Then you have the...

03:08.043 --> 03:10.032
Gracias, gracias, mucho gracias.

03:10.033 --> 03:11.902
Then you have the meet and
greet with the Pumas soccer

03:11.903 --> 03:14.684
team, and then you have dinner the mayor.

03:14.685 --> 03:17.873
Hey, hi. "Hai Lai," do you
know how to make God laugh?

03:17.874 --> 03:19.383
You tickle him.

03:19.384 --> 03:21.301
No, no, you don't tickle him
because he's not ticklish.

03:21.302 --> 03:22.284
Everybody knows that.

03:22.285 --> 03:23.699
I'll show you how.

03:23.700 --> 03:25.114
- Come, come, come, come.
- Wait, where are you going?

03:25.115 --> 03:26.840
Come, "Hai Lai," come, come, come.

03:26.841 --> 03:30.077
"Hai Lai, Hai Lai."

03:30.078 --> 03:32.523
You're getting on the bus?

03:32.524 --> 03:36.033
[mutters] yes, yes, yes, come, come, come.

03:40.244 --> 03:43.361
"Hai Lai," you're just seeing
the little tip of the iceberg.

03:43.362 --> 03:45.518
Mexico's this amazing, vast country,

03:45.519 --> 03:47.916
so rich, so transversal, so contradictory,

03:47.917 --> 03:50.602
full of mythology, full
of an amazing narrative.

03:50.603 --> 03:53.647
I think you will appreciate it.
Look, look, that guy, that guy,

03:53.648 --> 03:54.966
for example, the chubby guy?

03:54.967 --> 03:57.052
- Yeah.
- He's Tlaloc, the god of rain.

03:57.053 --> 03:59.569
Oh, he reminds me very much of
this god we have in my country,

03:59.570 --> 04:03.094
the great god SpongeBob.

04:03.095 --> 04:05.084
Oh, it's so good to see
you smile, "Hai Lai."

04:05.085 --> 04:06.379
I smile.

04:06.380 --> 04:07.650
No, you've been a little bit,

04:07.651 --> 04:09.304
you know, grouchy recently.

04:09.305 --> 04:11.870
Yeah, it's my fault, okay?
I put you to work a lot,

04:11.871 --> 04:15.035
but today I'm taking you
to a very special place.

04:15.036 --> 04:16.952
Where?

04:16.954 --> 04:18.559
Home.

04:18.560 --> 04:20.238
[phone rings]

04:20.238 --> 04:21.964
Well, how's my favorite hard-ass lawyer?

04:21.964 --> 04:24.913
How's it going, world traveler?

04:24.914 --> 04:28.558
You know, honestly, I can't
wait to get home to you,

04:28.559 --> 04:31.363
but the show last night was amazing.

04:31.364 --> 04:32.898
Oh, I know.

04:32.899 --> 04:35.200
The Latin rhythms, I mean,
you totally nailed it.

04:35.201 --> 04:37.166
I was smiling the whole time.

04:37.167 --> 04:40.547
Right, what are you talking about?

04:40.548 --> 04:42.776
I was there.

04:42.777 --> 04:45.846
[laughs]

04:45.847 --> 04:47.116
What are you doing for lunch?

04:47.117 --> 04:48.963
Where the hell is Rodrigo?

04:48.964 --> 04:50.641
You've got to be patient, Gloria.

04:50.642 --> 04:52.152
It's hard to be king.

04:52.153 --> 04:53.854
No, I think I'll rock the
track suit one more day.

04:53.855 --> 04:56.444
Apparently Virgil saw Rodrigo
and Hailey leave the hotel

04:56.445 --> 04:57.954
over an hour ago.

04:57.955 --> 04:59.225
They jumped on a bus?

04:59.226 --> 05:00.496
- Oh, great.
- Well, that's okay.

05:00.497 --> 05:02.198
It's just you and me, baby.

05:02.199 --> 05:03.996
Come on, let's go, just like the old days.

05:03.997 --> 05:07.569
[mariachi music]

05:07.570 --> 05:15.323
♪

05:17.000 --> 05:23.074
