06:03.845 --> 06:06.050
- [sighs]
- Hello.

06:06.051 --> 06:08.184
Welcome, Ms. Windsor. This way, please.

06:08.185 --> 06:10.054
- Wonderful.
- Oh, God.

06:10.055 --> 06:11.613
Come, Thomas.

06:11.614 --> 06:13.938
You don't think we're
gonna be whacked, do you?

06:13.939 --> 06:16.744
Señora, where are you taking us?

06:16.745 --> 06:19.861
Mr. Delgado will join you
in under one minute, Madame.

06:19.862 --> 06:23.385
[helicopter blades whirring]

06:23.386 --> 06:26.934
So Maestro was too busy
to join us? Unfortunate.

06:26.935 --> 06:29.188
Oh, he sends his deepest apologies.

06:29.189 --> 06:32.905
A matter of urgent
personal importance came up.

06:32.906 --> 06:35.446
Of course. Tell me, what is her name?

06:35.447 --> 06:39.378
Oh, you know the Maestro?

06:39.379 --> 06:42.759
I want to thank you, Juan
Luis, for meeting with us.

06:42.760 --> 06:45.756
As you know, we have a proposition.

06:45.757 --> 06:47.075
It's a beautiful country, yes?

06:47.076 --> 06:49.449
You know, Ted Turner has
about 2 million acres,

06:49.450 --> 06:54.484
which is nice if you didn't
have 3 million like I do.

06:54.485 --> 06:56.579
[speaking Spanish]

06:58.010 --> 06:59.423
Oh.

06:59.424 --> 07:01.030
Okay, you see that down there?

07:01.031 --> 07:02.612
Do we have a choice?

07:02.613 --> 07:06.689
That is where I'm creating
the largest mestengo sanctuary

07:06.690 --> 07:08.511
in the entire world.

07:08.512 --> 07:10.789
It is my pride and joy.

07:10.790 --> 07:12.731
You call them mustangs.

07:12.732 --> 07:14.553
Wild horses.

07:14.554 --> 07:16.639
"Couldn't drag me away."

07:16.640 --> 07:18.581
Ah, you like the Stones, huh?

07:18.582 --> 07:20.380
They played at my daughter's quinceañera.

07:20.381 --> 07:22.538
Well, Mick played at my wedding

07:22.539 --> 07:24.792
with half the bridesmaids.

07:24.793 --> 07:29.155
Definitely got a bit of satisfaction there.

07:29.156 --> 07:33.016
Not to drag you two wild horses away,

07:33.017 --> 07:35.174
but, um, everyone knows that MexiMundial

07:35.175 --> 07:38.147
is looking to penetrate
the American market,

07:38.148 --> 07:41.528
and if you should decide
to buy the naming rights

07:41.529 --> 07:43.374
to our new symphony hall,

07:43.375 --> 07:48.466
we could create a very lucrative
synergy between our two brands.

07:50.113 --> 07:52.773
Yes, Si, no, what you are saying is...

07:52.774 --> 07:54.188
it's very practical.

07:54.189 --> 07:57.760
My marketing team will be very pleased.

07:57.761 --> 07:59.679
Oh, yes, of course, what...

07:59.680 --> 08:02.604
but the cross-promotional opportunities...

08:02.605 --> 08:05.625
Gloria, shh, please stop.

08:05.626 --> 08:08.095
Quit while you're behind.

08:08.096 --> 08:12.171
You're right, wild horses need sanctuaries,

08:12.172 --> 08:14.664
but so do wild artists.

08:14.665 --> 08:18.405
Bach, Beethoven, Mozart,
they were all geniuses, sure,

08:18.406 --> 08:20.491
but they needed men of great vision

08:20.492 --> 08:23.929
to bring their genius
to the rest of the world.

08:26.630 --> 08:28.868
Do you mind if I plug in?

08:31.378 --> 08:35.501
[classical music playing]

08:35.501 --> 08:37.635
See, you don't buy bloody naming rights

08:37.635 --> 08:41.159
for some cross-promotional bullshit.

08:41.159 --> 08:43.965
You do it to let the music live.

08:43.966 --> 08:45.571
"La Boheme."

08:45.572 --> 08:48.041
"La Boheme," beautiful,

08:48.042 --> 08:50.846
and your name should
take its rightful place

08:50.847 --> 08:53.436
along the great patrons in history,

08:53.437 --> 08:55.138
Emperor Franz-Joseph,

08:55.139 --> 08:57.968
Cosimo de Medici,

08:57.969 --> 09:00.174
Juan Luis Delgado.

09:00.175 --> 09:02.188
Juan Luis de Medici, I like it.

09:02.189 --> 09:04.370
Oh, fucking A, you do.

09:04.371 --> 09:06.887
You're pretty crazy, huh, Pembrook?

09:06.888 --> 09:11.395
Yeah, Pembridge, actually, but yes,

09:11.396 --> 09:13.745
crazy like a fox.

09:13.746 --> 09:15.375
[laughter]

09:15.376 --> 09:16.958
You know what?

09:16.959 --> 09:21.298
I say we make this
beautiful music together.

09:21.299 --> 09:22.640
Yes.

09:22.641 --> 09:26.860
♪

09:26.861 --> 09:29.858
I thought that you grew up
in Mexico City with Manu.

09:29.859 --> 09:31.296
Yeah, I grew up with Manu,

09:31.297 --> 09:33.502
but then, you know, we would
get into so much trouble,

09:33.503 --> 09:38.609
and my parents send me here
to my grandmother's right here.

09:38.610 --> 09:40.456
Is she still alive?

09:40.457 --> 09:42.062
Ho, she's so alive.

09:42.063 --> 09:45.227
You'll see. She's, like, incredibly alive.

09:45.228 --> 09:47.082
Okay, I got it.

09:50.503 --> 09:52.612
- It's so beautiful.
- You like it?

09:52.613 --> 09:55.369
Yeah, it's, like, from
another time or something.

09:55.370 --> 09:59.110
Yeah, it's like this since I was a kid.

09:59.111 --> 10:02.131
- Hey.
- [speaking Spanish]

10:02.132 --> 10:04.778
[both speaking Spanish]

10:21.458 --> 10:22.608
I didn't have the courtesy

10:22.609 --> 10:24.439
to tell you that I was coming.

10:28.939 --> 10:29.978
Ah, perfecto.

10:44.932 --> 10:47.832
[classical music]

10:47.833 --> 10:55.778
♪

10:57.640 --> 11:00.660
I wish that we'd come here
before the performance.

11:00.661 --> 11:02.003
Why?

11:02.004 --> 11:04.041
Because I would have played
it with a different feeling.

11:04.042 --> 11:07.167
Better? Better than you did?

11:10.611 --> 11:13.488
Ah, she wants us to go to
the market and get some meat,

11:13.489 --> 11:15.142
which is cecina,

11:15.143 --> 11:16.869
and two onions and some avocados,

11:16.870 --> 11:18.571
and don't let me choose them.

11:18.572 --> 11:20.092
Eh, abuelita, [speaking Spanish].

11:21.689 --> 11:24.325
- Can I ask you something?
- Mm-hmm.

11:24.326 --> 11:27.251
Seducing the union committee chair,

11:27.252 --> 11:30.200
is that standard negotiating procedure?

11:30.201 --> 11:34.732
Honestly, I've never done this before.

11:34.733 --> 11:36.218
- You don't believe me.
- I don't know.

11:36.219 --> 11:38.904
I mean, you seem like someone
who plots out every move.

11:38.905 --> 11:41.445
- Oh.
- Which is not a criticism.

11:41.446 --> 11:42.644
Well, you're right.

11:42.645 --> 11:46.600
Normally I have everything all worked out,

11:46.601 --> 11:51.573
but, well, something about
you makes me want to improvise.

11:56.528 --> 11:58.526
[phone ringing]

12:03.098 --> 12:05.878
Bob, hey, I was just about to call you.

12:05.879 --> 12:07.581
Uh, I'm in the lobby. I'm early, I know,

12:07.582 --> 12:10.122
but whenever you're ready, no pressure.

12:10.123 --> 12:11.225
Uh, you know, I'm...

12:11.226 --> 12:12.232
I'm just not feeling well.

12:12.233 --> 12:14.103
I'm in bed, but you should go.

12:14.104 --> 12:15.182
- Take Dee Dee.
- Well...

12:15.183 --> 12:16.596
Have fun.

12:16.597 --> 12:18.203
I'm not gonna go without you, Cyn.

12:18.204 --> 12:20.241
- I don't even like Mexican food.
- I'm sorry.

12:20.242 --> 12:25.612
I... you know, maybe next time.

12:25.613 --> 12:27.530
- Feel better.
- Good night.

12:27.531 --> 12:28.849
I feel terrible.

12:28.850 --> 12:30.407
He got this reservation
at this great place,

12:30.408 --> 12:31.438
and now he's not even going.

12:31.439 --> 12:33.692
- What place?
- Uh, Limo...

12:33.693 --> 12:35.227
- Limo Cineros?
- Si.

12:35.228 --> 12:37.361
Oh, my God, that place
is supposed to be amazing.

12:37.362 --> 12:40.310
Oh, there's no way we're
giving up that reservation.

12:40.311 --> 12:42.612
- Chin-chin.
- It was just like the old days,

12:42.613 --> 12:44.122
Thomas. You were soaring.

12:44.123 --> 12:47.695
Mm, just another bloody
lion in winter, darling,

12:47.696 --> 12:49.973
but hey, listen, I appreciate it.

12:49.974 --> 12:51.124
Thank you.

12:51.125 --> 12:52.562
Excuse me just a moment, all right?

12:52.563 --> 12:54.169
I'll be right back.

12:54.170 --> 12:55.176
We just sat down.

12:55.177 --> 12:57.166
The girl's room.

12:57.167 --> 12:58.988
You gonna powder your nose?

12:58.989 --> 13:03.112
Ooh, what a nice ass.

13:03.113 --> 13:04.191
Hey, Bobby, Bobby,

13:04.192 --> 13:06.014
Bobby come here.

13:06.015 --> 13:07.452
Pavel, can't you see I'm busy with work?

13:07.453 --> 13:10.353
Ah, yes, you're very busy with the old man.

13:10.354 --> 13:13.423
I thought we were gonna
spend the afternoon together.

13:13.424 --> 13:15.221
- And we will.
- Yeah?

13:15.222 --> 13:18.074
Thomas and I were just
having a celebratory drink.

13:18.075 --> 13:19.537
We landed Delgado.

13:19.538 --> 13:22.126
Wonderful, then I join you.

13:22.127 --> 13:24.596
I...

13:24.597 --> 13:26.442
Oh, I see.

13:26.443 --> 13:28.720
I'm sorry I'm not one of your rich donors

13:28.721 --> 13:30.303
or dissolute ex-conductors

13:30.304 --> 13:33.588
you flirt with for money or influence.

13:33.589 --> 13:34.954
Don't make this a class issue.

13:34.955 --> 13:40.373
In my country, I'm biochemical engineer.

13:40.374 --> 13:43.068
- Pavel.
- Ah, no more words.

13:46.752 --> 13:49.149
You know what this is? This
is the place where I met...

13:49.150 --> 13:51.283
where I met Maestro Rivera, around here.

13:51.284 --> 13:53.081
- In this market?
- Yeah.

13:53.082 --> 13:54.448
- In the market?
- I used to come with... yeah,

13:54.449 --> 13:56.414
with some friends, you
know, play music, and then...

13:56.415 --> 13:57.973
[speaks Spanish]

13:57.974 --> 14:01.114
And then... and we... you know,

14:01.115 --> 14:03.799
this guy comes up and says
"I've got a music school.

14:03.800 --> 14:05.837
Are you guys interested?" and then

14:05.838 --> 14:07.779
- started to talk about Mozart.
- Oh.

14:07.780 --> 14:11.256
And that's how everything came about, okay?

14:11.257 --> 14:12.886
- Nope.
- How many did she...

14:12.887 --> 14:14.109
You really don't know
how to choose an avocado?

14:14.110 --> 14:17.490
Ay, "Hai Lai," honestly?

14:17.491 --> 14:20.943
You have to... okay, take this.

14:20.944 --> 14:22.525
You have to pull out this part,

14:22.526 --> 14:25.019
and if it's green, then it's ripe.

14:25.020 --> 14:27.537
- And then what?
- And then you buy it,

14:27.538 --> 14:28.592
- and you eat it.
- And then what?

14:28.593 --> 14:29.743
And then... [laughs]

14:29.744 --> 14:32.404
That was the most delicious meal.

14:32.405 --> 14:34.034
Muchos gracias.

14:34.035 --> 14:39.070
Ah, you are... welcome.

14:39.071 --> 14:44.474
[speaking Spanish] Bien, bien.

14:46.743 --> 14:49.236
Should we help to clean up?

14:49.237 --> 14:50.267
[speaking Spanish]

14:50.268 --> 14:51.682
Ah, wait, wait.

14:51.683 --> 14:53.753
- Is something wrong?
- No, no.

14:55.735 --> 14:57.364
See, she's reading the cup.

14:57.365 --> 14:58.899
Okay, well, if I'm gonna get hit by a bus,

14:58.900 --> 15:00.994
she really doesn't need to tell me, so...

15:30.214 --> 15:35.153
- I... ay, ay, "Hai Lai."
- Yeah?

15:35.154 --> 15:39.253
She said... okay, she said many things.

15:39.254 --> 15:40.668
She said that there's a lot

15:40.669 --> 15:42.778
of love and confusion
and passion for music,

15:42.779 --> 15:44.960
and that we are gonna have a big career,

15:44.961 --> 15:46.015
and you especially.

15:46.016 --> 15:48.508
You're gonna... like, yeah.

15:48.509 --> 15:50.340
- That's great.
- Yeah, yeah.

15:55.223 --> 15:58.771
Oh, no, no, no, no, no, thank you so much,

15:58.772 --> 16:00.545
but these are too beautiful.

16:00.546 --> 16:02.496
I would... you should keep them.

16:08.195 --> 16:11.047
Gracias.

16:11.048 --> 16:12.198
Thank you.

16:12.199 --> 16:15.099
You are welcome.

16:15.100 --> 16:17.065
I wanted to play the French horn,

16:17.066 --> 16:19.127
but my mother thought I'd rupture a lung,

16:19.128 --> 16:21.525
so she bought me a piccolo,
and the rest is history.

16:21.526 --> 16:23.875
So your mother bought
you your first piccolo?

16:23.876 --> 16:25.697
I know, believe me, I know.

16:25.698 --> 16:27.687
You know, we've worked
together for ten years.

16:27.688 --> 16:31.260
We've never had a Mano-a-Mano moment.

16:31.261 --> 16:33.082
- Gracias.
- Why is Mexican food

16:33.083 --> 16:35.864
so much better in Mexico?

16:35.865 --> 16:37.830
Gracias.

16:37.831 --> 16:38.846
Gracias.

16:41.571 --> 16:43.186
Holy shite.

16:45.384 --> 16:47.588
- So this is awkward.
- Oh, good.

16:47.589 --> 16:49.986
Well, thank you for sparing us the

16:49.987 --> 16:51.617
"It's not what you think" line.

16:51.618 --> 16:53.319
- I thought you were in bed.
- I was.

16:53.320 --> 16:55.237
- She was.
- Oh, yeah, in bed?

16:55.238 --> 16:57.419
Oh, the two... wow.

16:57.420 --> 17:01.280
I guess maybe that makes
us piccolo brothers.

17:01.281 --> 17:03.893
Cyn, can I talk to you for a second?

17:03.894 --> 17:05.666
Sure. Excuse me.

17:05.667 --> 17:09.311
Thanks. Excuse us, Counselor.

17:09.313 --> 17:12.869
Well, I wonder what that
makes us, Mr. Pembridge.

17:15.211 --> 17:16.411
Since when?

17:16.412 --> 17:18.136
It started a couple of
weeks before we left on tour.

17:18.137 --> 17:21.421
Look, it really has nothing to do with you.

17:21.422 --> 17:24.106
Yes, it does. She's our negotiator.

17:24.107 --> 17:25.832
She's supposed to be representing us,

17:25.833 --> 17:26.911
not sleeping with the boss.

17:26.912 --> 17:28.061
You should know better, Cyn.

17:28.063 --> 17:29.741
I don't need a lecture from you, Bob.

17:29.742 --> 17:31.323
I get it.

17:31.324 --> 17:34.344
You don't need anything
from me. Come on, Thomas.

17:34.345 --> 17:36.478
Let's go find another place to eat.

17:36.479 --> 17:38.588
Yeah, of all the taquerias

17:38.589 --> 17:40.938
in all the towns in all the world, huh?

17:40.939 --> 17:41.825
Yeah.

17:41.826 --> 17:44.975
[man speaking Spanish on TV]

17:51.417 --> 17:52.903
Come, come.

17:52.904 --> 17:54.174
You're gonna sleep here tonight, okay?

17:54.175 --> 17:55.502
- Thank you.
- Yeah.

18:00.265 --> 18:03.597
Wow.

18:03.598 --> 18:06.474
It's amazing how similar your room is

18:06.475 --> 18:10.574
- to my room growing up.
- Really?

18:10.575 --> 18:13.643
Yeah, I mean, except I didn't have soccer.

18:13.644 --> 18:15.082
I had a lot of Backstreet Boys,

18:15.083 --> 18:17.456
and I had a Chopin bobble head, so...

18:17.457 --> 18:20.836
What did you expect my room to be like?

18:20.837 --> 18:22.755
I don't know, cooler?

18:22.756 --> 18:26.855
"Hai Lai," I'm sorry to burst your bubble.

18:26.856 --> 18:30.005
I'm a nerd just like you.

19:29.676 --> 19:31.315
Buenos noches.

19:33.920 --> 19:36.821
[classical music]

19:36.822 --> 19:44.766
♪

20:03.700 --> 20:04.994
All the donations have helped a lot

20:04.995 --> 20:06.505
to change the place a little bit.

20:06.506 --> 20:08.807
We have here the washer and dryer.

20:08.808 --> 20:11.852
Huh, the... yeah, finally
somebody appreciated it.

20:11.853 --> 20:16.527
And my room is totally reconstructed.

20:16.528 --> 20:22.354
My new library, my new
bed, the TV, and it's...

20:22.355 --> 20:25.639
it's very cozy, isn't it, Hailey?

20:25.640 --> 20:28.429
It's very cozy.

20:49.161 --> 20:50.896
Ah.

20:52.902 --> 20:56.291
Come, come, come to the royal box.

21:00.119 --> 21:02.995
