21:02.996 --> 21:10.965
♪

21:22.970 --> 21:23.985
[music stops]

21:33.927 --> 21:36.084
No, no.

21:36.085 --> 21:38.602
- Por favor?
- No, Maestro, no.

21:38.603 --> 21:39.834
Por favor.

21:42.895 --> 21:43.934
Bueno.

21:49.369 --> 21:50.576
¿Listos?

21:53.013 --> 22:00.886
♪

22:24.687 --> 22:32.632
♪

23:18.540 --> 23:25.670
♪

23:27.892 --> 23:29.315
Maestro...

23:33.718 --> 23:34.973
Gracias.

24:03.138 --> 24:06.240
I... Maestro, I...

24:31.815 --> 24:34.620
I can't because I have the
orchestra, and they need me.

24:34.621 --> 24:37.281
"Hai Lai," she's one
of our youngest members.

24:37.282 --> 24:38.921
She needs me, and...

25:31.423 --> 25:34.779
Hey, "Hai Lai," I am very sorry.

25:34.780 --> 25:37.162
- For what?
- Eh.

25:40.630 --> 25:45.401
Ladies and gentlemen, welcome
to flight 115 Lina Americana,

25:45.402 --> 25:49.285
nonstop service to New York
City's John F. Kennedy airport.

25:49.286 --> 25:50.364
We will be taking off shortly.

25:50.365 --> 25:51.803
- "Hai Lai?"
- Oh, hey.

25:51.804 --> 25:53.146
- Hey, how do you feel?
- Uh, I feel good.

25:53.147 --> 25:54.464
I feel a little wiped out, but...

25:54.465 --> 25:56.167
No, yeah, but I feel I caught something.

25:56.168 --> 25:59.164
You know, I might have...
have something here.

25:59.165 --> 26:02.425
I'm sorry about what
happened with Maestro Rivera.

26:02.426 --> 26:04.415
Yeah, that was awful, right?

26:04.416 --> 26:06.069
Ugh, that was really bad.

26:06.070 --> 26:07.676
Yeah.

26:07.677 --> 26:10.337
Do you remember when we went
to my grandmother's house,

26:10.338 --> 26:11.584
that we went to my room,

26:11.585 --> 26:13.311
- my... when I was a kid?
- Yeah.

26:13.312 --> 26:15.013
Full of posters, you know,
and we made the bed togeth...

26:15.014 --> 26:16.068
Yeah, no, I remember. It happened.

26:16.069 --> 26:18.586
It's not our real lives.

26:18.587 --> 26:23.486
I also... I realized that you're
a really shitty translator.

26:25.037 --> 26:26.234
"Hai Lai"?

26:26.235 --> 26:29.112
What... could you tell what
my grandmother was saying?

26:29.113 --> 26:31.437
Yeah, two years of high school Spanish

26:31.438 --> 26:34.219
goes a really long way, it turns out.

26:34.220 --> 26:36.233
Ay, "Hai Lai."

26:36.234 --> 26:38.343
It's okay, father of my children.

26:38.344 --> 26:40.189
- Ay, no. I...
- We have a really long time.

26:40.190 --> 26:41.316
That's what the coffee grounds said.

26:41.317 --> 26:42.563
- Excuse me?
- Yes?

26:42.564 --> 26:43.594
- Sir?
- Yes?

26:43.595 --> 26:44.769
Sorry, you have to go back to your seat.

26:44.770 --> 26:47.742
Ay, thank you.

26:47.743 --> 26:52.034
Well, "Hai Lai," see you...

26:52.035 --> 26:52.993
see you there.

26:52.994 --> 26:54.033
Okay.

26:56.423 --> 26:57.693
- Look what I found in...
- Oh, it's lovely.

26:57.694 --> 26:59.419
- It's a good picture.
- Arts section.

